I hope I'm not grossing anyone out, but her are some photos of my recent exploits. 1-brand new left hip joint. 2-fracture of the femur that prompted the me hip. 3-scar from surgery. And as a good friend says, easy as falling off a bicycle! Kudos to the great Drs and nurses at #parkviewmc in pueblo for their great care, and to Dr Likes and his staff for his surgical skills and their care.
#potterslife #bicycle #hipreplacement #femurfollies

Watch thru to see some new wall sculpture just uploaded to artful home's website today. These were fired a couple of months ago, but the hip is feeling better and maybe I can do some firing soon!

While this bikes pedals helped me break my hip, it is now, next to clay, my biggest salvation! My surgeon when he released me said riding a bike was great therapy for the new hip, and I ride 45 to 75 minutes a day 5 days a week on it! I really credit it with my fast recovery. Just wish bike manufacturers made bigger bikes!

Went for a ride on my new bike last Saturday afternoon. Low forties but kept warm enough. Saw a bald eagle and a four point mule deer chasing another four point mulie, forty feet off to my right! Quite a day. New bike is a KHS Flite 747 XL with a frame designed for people 6'4" to 6'7" tall.
So much nicer to ride a bike that fits! Thank you @zinncycles .
